Sixteen-year-old US-based Marylove Edwards on Thursday caused a major upset at the ongoing 43rd Central Bank of Nigeria Senior Tennis Open Championship when she stopped former winner and Edo 2020 National Sports Festival champion Sarah Adegoke (6-2 retired) to reach the semi-finals.  No.9 seed Adegoke could not continue the game due to injury. Top seed and women’s singles defending champion, Oyinlomo Quadri, also outclassed  Ronke Akingbade 6-0, 6-1 to advance. The men’s singles champion and tournament top seed, Joseph Imeh, defeated Clifford Enesoregbe (5-0 retired) to cruise into the quarter-finals, while Nonso Madueke earned a 6-4, 6-1 victory over Ojo Oyelami to also cruise to the next round. Third seed Musa Mohammed came from a set down to beat 2014 winner Henry Atseye 4-6, 7-6, 6-2, while Thomas Otu recorded a comeback 3-6, 6-3, 6-2 win over veteran Shehu Lawal. Micheal Chima beat Peter Lawal 6-0, 6-2 to also progress. In the wheelchair category, Alex Adewale beat Ajani Idowu 4-0, 4-1 in one of the men’s singles match-up, while Simon Promise sent Kayode Samuel packing via a 4-0, 4-0 defeat. Also victorious was Chituru Nwaozuzu, who defeated Joy Ogun 4-0, 4-0, while Justina Ofoha was bundled out by Kafayat Omisore 4-1.4-1in the women’s singles event of the wheelchair category. All the quarter-final matches were decided ahead of today’s semi-finals, while the finals of the various events are billed for Saturday. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com